# Harness warmup (Grace-Mar)

New Cursor threads have **no memory** of `recursion-gate`, `self-evidence`, or `session-log`. Warmup fixes that.

## When to run

At the **start of a new chat** when work touches **instance state** (pipeline, RECURSION-GATE, Voice, OpenClaw handoff, `users/grace-mar/`, bootstrap continuation):

1. Run from repo root:
   ```bash
   python3 scripts/harness_warmup.py -u grace-mar
   ```
   Use `--compact` if the operator prefers one paragraph. **`--territory wap`** = work-political-consulting pending only; **`companion`** = Record pending only (see `recursion_gate_territory.py`).

2. **Include the command output** in your reply (paste verbatim or as a fenced markdown block) so the thread carries the same snapshot.

## When you may skip

- Operator says they’re only editing unrelated code/docs with no gate/evidence context.
- Warmup was already pasted in this thread.
- Trivial one-line fix with no Record/pipeline involvement.

## Relation to bootstrap

`grace-mar-bootstrap.md` = **procedure** (what to read, work-build-ai, commands). Warmup = **current state** (pending candidates, last ACT, session tail). They stack: bootstrap orients; warmup grounds.

## Do not

- Merge or stage from warmup output — it’s read-only context.
- Treat warmup text as Record truth; canonical files remain `users/grace-mar/*.md`.
